This article is a readout by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs on the President's bilateral meeting with President Lula of Brazil. The meeting lasted about 30 minutes and they discussed four primary topics: energy and climate, Honduras, the economy, and Iran. They agreed to continue working together on climate change leading up to the Copenhagen summit. They also discussed the crisis in Honduras and thanked Brazil for their coordination. In terms of the economy, they talked about steps to bring the global economy back on track and the upcoming G20 meeting. Lastly, they discussed Iran and the unique opportunity Brazil has to reiterate the message approved at the G8. The article also mentions that President Lula expressed relief that Brazil did not lose to the US in soccer.